description:
"The Build: The Challenge To Create On the Same Scale As We Can Destroy" by Gene Youngblood at the 2016 Gray Area Festival.

Summon the breathtaking image of the multitude pouring into streets and plazas around the world in millions to demonstrate against tyranny. Now imagine instead theyâ€™re demanding a free and open internet. The likelihood of that is almost zero, we would agree. But why is that?  What would have to happen to make that utopian spectacle reality? What insurgent algorithm would get us from here to there?

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io

Videographer, Bryan Konefsky

Gray Area

chapters.title: The Build Creating on the same scale as we can destroy
Socialized, toll-free, public internet Content separate from Conduit Symmetrical emotional bandwidth End to End Encryption Translocal social heterotopias

THE BROADCAST All state media, their institutional infrastructure. their political economy, the culture they create. and the social control the culture serves through the socialization it administers.
THE ECOSOCIAL CRISIS Ecological holocaust Capitalist globalism End of democracy Rise of the internet
A map of the world that does not include utopia is not worth even glancing at. for it leaves out the one country at which humanity is always landing.
THE UTOPIAN MYTH OF A COMMUNICATION REVOLUTION
